cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper is about improving the training of feedforward neural networks with random hidden nodes using a data-driven approach. The paper focuses on the optimization of the network architecture and the generation of random weights and biases. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of the network for classification tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for adjusting the network architecture during the training process, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed method on several application examples, which could also suggest that it belongs to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
